# Filtrar para obtener solo Argentina
argentina=countries[countries.COUNTRY=='Argentina']
In [9]:
# Clipping de ciudades y ríos para Argentina
citiesArgentina_clipped = gpd.clip(gdf=cities,
                          mask=argentina)
riversArgentina_clipped = gpd.clip(gdf=rivers,
                               mask=argentina)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Base plot de Argentina
base = argentina.plot(facecolor="greenyellow", edgecolor='black', linewidth=0.4,figsize=(5,5))

                    ax=base)

# Plotear ríos recortados en Argentina
riversArgentina_clipped.plot(edgecolor='blue', linewidth=0.5,
                    ax=base)

import os

# Guardar las capas reproyectadas
argentina_9252.to_file(os.path.join("maps","argentinaMaps_9252.gpkg"), layer='country', driver="GPKG")

rivers_argentina_9252.to_file(os.path.join("maps","argentinaMaps_9252.gpkg"), layer='rivers', driver="GPKG")
argentina_9252.centroid.to_file(os.path.join("maps","argentinaMaps_9252.gpkg"), layer='centroid', driver="GPKG")

Exercise 7¶

3. Turn the hull into a GDF.¶

In [55]:
from shapely.geometry import MultiPoint

def plot_convex_hull(quadrant, quadrant_name, ax):
    if len(quadrant) > 2:  # Necesitamos al menos 3 puntos para formar un polígono
        points = MultiPoint([point for point in quadrant.geometry])
        hull = points.convex_hull
        hull_gdf = gpd.GeoDataFrame(geometry=[hull], crs=quadrant.crs)
        hull_gdf.plot(ax=ax, edgecolor='white', alpha=0.4, facecolor='none', hatch='X')
        print(f"Convex hull plotted for {quadrant_name}")
    else:
        print(f"Not enough points to form a convex hull in {quadrant_name}")

fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 1, figsize=(10, 10))
argentina_9252.plot(ax=ax, facecolor='yellow', edgecolor='black')

plot_convex_hull(top_left, 'Top Left', ax)
plot_convex_hull(top_right, 'Top Right', ax)
plot_convex_hull(bottom_left, 'Bottom Left', ax)
plot_convex_hull(bottom_right, 'Bottom Right', ax)

plt.show()

# Filtrar aeropuertos grandes y medianos
large_and_medium_airports = airports_9252[airports_9252['type'].isin(['large_airport', 'medium_airport'])]

# Crear el convex hull para los aeropuertos grandes y medianos
if len(large_and_medium_airports) > 2:  # Necesitamos al menos 3 puntos para formar un polígono
    large_and_medium_airports_points = MultiPoint([point for point in large_and_medium_airports.geometry])
    large_and_medium_airports_hull = large_and_medium_airports_points.convex_hull
    
    # Convertir el convex hull a un GeoDataFrame
    large_and_medium_airports_hull_gdf = gpd.GeoDataFrame(geometry=[large_and_medium_airports_hull], crs=large_and_medium_airports.crs)
    large_and_medium_airports_hull_gdf['name'] = 'Large and Medium Airports Hull'  # Nombre opcional

    print("Convex hull created for large and medium airports")
else:
    print("Not enough points to form a convex hull for large and medium airports")
